But the earlier summary bullet in the idempotency section still says compensation happens on a non-transport store error, with ÔÇťa 409 `invalid-precondition` returned and receivedÔÇŁ as the example, without repeating the new different-SHA carveout. Since different-SHA is also a synchronous `invalid-precondition`, that sentence is still broader than the later rule. Tighten that one example to say ÔÇťnon-divergence `invalid-precondition`ÔÇŁ or similar, and the document will be consistent throughout. Ref: [eden-phase-8a-wire-protocol.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-8a-wire-protocol.md:185)
